  <name>PulseCaster</name>
  <_summary>Record a podcast interview or the sound from a meeting</_summary>
  <description>
    <_p>PulseCaster is a PulseAudio-based sound recorder. You can use it to record podcasts, interviews or videoconferencing meetings happening on your Linux computer.</_p>
    <_p>PulseCaster allows you to select which sources to use for recording (ex.: which microphone device for your voice, and which playback device to get your subject's voice from your separate audio/videoconferencing app). It then automatically mixes the sound sources into one ready-to-publish recording.</_p>
    <_p>There is also an expert mode so you can mix or enhance the recording on your own.</_p>
  </description>
